The cylinder has:
- Length along x: 2 units
- Diameter: 0.4 units
- Offset in y: 0.6 units (so center at y=0.6)
- Wall thickness: 0.07 → inner radius = 0.2, outer radius = 0.27
- We need 4 blocks around the circumference

Vertices: 16 total (4×4 grid at z=-0.07 and z=0.07)
- At z=-0.07: x = [-1,-0.3,0.3,1], y = [-0.4, 0.4] → vertices 0,1,2,3 and 4,5,6,7
- At z=0.07: x = [-1,-0.3,0.3,1], y = [-0.4, 0.4] → vertices 8,9,10,11 and 12,13,14,15

Each hex block is `hex (i j k l m n o p)` where (i,j,k,l) is one face and (m,n,o,p) is the opposite face, with the right-hand rule ensuring outward-pointing faces.

